Citation.sTitle: Vapor Pressures and Sublimation Enthalpies of Cadmium Difluoride and Zinc Difluoride by the Torsion-Effusion Method
Citation.sAbstract: The vapor pressures over solid CdF2 and ZnF2 were measured by the torsion-effusion method. The temperature dependencies of the vapor pressures of these compounds were found to fit the following equations: log(p/ kPa) ) (9.55 ( 0.30) - (13920 ( 300)(T/K) (from (962 to 1149) K), and log(p/kPa) ) (9.79 ( 0.40) - (12510 ( 400)(T/K) (from (846 to 1047) K) for CdF2 and ZnF2, respectively. Treating these vapor pressures by the second- and third-law methods, the standard sublimation enthalpies AsubHdeg (298 K) ) (285 ( 10) kJ * mol-1 and (257 ( 8) kJ * mol-1 and entropies AsubSdeg (298 K) ) (163 ( 6) J *K-1 * mol-1 and (169 ( 8) J *K-1 * mol-1 for CdF2 and ZnF2, respectively, were calculated.
